Tech Stack for AI Chatbot with Vector Search for Release Notes
Backend & API
ğŸ”¹ Python (FastAPI/Flask) â€“ For building the chatbot backend
ğŸ”¹ LangChain â€“ For handling LLM-powered search & responses
ğŸ”¹ OpenAI/GPT â€“ For AI-based text generation & summarization
ğŸ”¹ Faiss / Pinecone / ChromaDB â€“ For vector database & similarity search
ğŸ”¹ GitHub API â€“ To fetch commits, pull requests, and issues

Data Processing & Storage
ğŸ”¹ Hugging Face Sentence Transformers â€“ For converting text into embeddings
ğŸ”¹ PostgreSQL / MongoDB â€“ To store structured release notes
ğŸ”¹ Redis / Memcached â€“ For caching frequently searched results

Frontend & Integration
ğŸ”¹ React.js / Next.js â€“ For UI if you want a web-based chatbot
ğŸ”¹ Slack API â€“ For real-time Slack integration
ğŸ”¹ Docker & Kubernetes â€“ For containerization and deployment

Why Use LangChain?
âœ… Simplifies Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG) â€“ Helps in fetching relevant GitHub commits, PRs, and issues using vector search.
âœ… Integrates with FAISS / ChromaDB â€“ Allows you to efficiently search embedded release notes.
âœ… Works with Open-Source LLMs â€“ Can use Mistral-7B, LLaMA 2, or Hugging Face Models instead of OpenAI.
âœ… Streamlines Data Processing â€“ Helps structure commits and PRs for better searchability.

How LangChain Fits into Your Chatbot Workflow
1ï¸âƒ£ User asks a question (e.g., "What new features were added in the last release?")
2ï¸âƒ£ LangChain converts the question into an embedding (using Hugging Face Sentence Transformers)
3ï¸âƒ£ FAISS/ChromaDB searches for similar commits, PRs, and issues
4ï¸âƒ£ Most relevant results are retrieved & formatted
5ï¸âƒ£ LangChain generates a structured response using a selected LLM
6ï¸âƒ£ Chatbot returns the formatted release notes